../files/moonlightghost/screenshot_0.png\" class = \"screenshot image\" alt = \"Screenshot image.\" />\n		</li>\n		<li class = \"no_2 item last\">\n			<img src = \"../files/moonlightghost/screenshot_1.png\" class = \"screenshot image\" alt = \"Screenshot image.\" />\n		</li>\n	</ul>\n</div>\";s:6:\"format\";s:9:\"full_html\";s:10:\"substitute\";i:1;}','a:0:{}','a:1:{s:8:\"settings\";N;}','a:0:{}','a:0:{}',0,'a:0:{}','245a4707-ab0f-4655-95a6-cd5f0ee80d9c'),(83,24,'right','custom','custom',1,'a:0:{}','a:5:{s:11:\"admin_title\";s:12:\"Right column\";s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"body\";s:8980:\"<div class = \"game_general_right_column_wrapper\">\n	<div class = \"description\">\n		<p>\n			Moonlight Ghost is a \"reverse horror game\" by tachi made in RPG Maker VX Ace.\n			This ends up making it a level-based high score arcade puzzle game. But not actually horror.\n		</p>\n		<p>\n			A reverse horror game, where you do the horror!\n			It\'s up to you, the player, to scare people!\n			It\'s a somewhat odd adventure game with four chapters in all.\n		</p>\n	</div>\n	<div class = \"bonus hide\">\n<div class = \'toggle-button\' onclick = \"var a = document.getElementsByClassName(\'bonus\')[0]; if(a.classList.contains(\'hide\')){a.classList.remove(\'hide\');}else{a.classList.add(\'hide\');}\">Toggle</div>\n		<h2>Bonus</h2>\n		<p>\n			Various information about the post-game chapter. Spoilers, probably.\n		</p>\n		<h3>\n			Rank Requirements\n		</h3>\n		<table>\n		<tbody><tr><td><b>Mission</b></td><td><b>Target</b></td><td><b>B/Clear</b></td><td><b>A Rank</b></td><td><b>S Rank</b></td></tr>\n		<tr><td>1</td><td>Girl</td><td>500</td><td>1100</td><td>1300</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>2</td><td>Date Man</td><td>500</td><td>900</td><td>1200</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>3</td><td>Old Man</td><td>250</td><td>450</td><td>600</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>4</td><td>Late Girl</td><td>250</td><td>550</td><td>800</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>5</td><td>Rascal</td><td>250</td><td>420</td><td>550</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>6</td><td>Mistress Act 1</td><td>250</td><td>420</td><td>550</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>7</td><td>Mistress Act 2</td><td>250</td><td>300</td><td>350</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>8</td><td>Mistress Act 3</td><td>500</td><td>700</td><td>900</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>9</td><td>Vampire Act 1</td><td>400</td><td>420</td><td>480</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>10</td><td>Vampire Act 2</td><td>400</td><td>420</td><td>480</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>11</td><td>Vampire Act 3</td><td>800</td><td>950</td><td>1100</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>12</td><td>Vampire Act 4</td><td>400</td><td>420</td><td>480</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>13</td><td>Final Battle</td><td>1000</td><td>1150</td><td>1350</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>14</td><td>Nightlife Girl</td><td>250</td><td>300</td><td>380</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>15</td><td>RPG Prince</td><td>250</td><td>300</td><td>380</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>16</td><td>Mighty Warrior</td><td>250</td><td>300</td><td>380</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>17</td><td>Date Man 2</td><td>250</td><td>300</td><td>380</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>18</td><td>Old Man 2</td><td>250</td><td>300</td><td>380</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>19</td><td>Late Girl 2</td><td>250</td><td>300</td><td>380</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>20</td><td>Rascal 2</td><td>250</td><td>300</td><td>380</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>21</td><td>Mistress 2</td><td>250</td><td>300</td><td>380</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>22</td><td>Girl 2</td><td>250</td><td>300</td><td>380</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>23</td><td>Spirit Queen</td><td>2500</td><td>2500</td><td>2500</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>24</td><td>Akari</td><td>1000</td><td>1000</td><td>1000</td></tr>\n		</tbody></table>\n		<h3>\n			Shop Levels\n		</h3>\n		<table>\n		<tbody><tr><td><b>Level</b></td><td><b>Total EXP</b></td></tr>\n		<tr><td>1</td><td>0</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>2</td><td>200</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>3</td><td>800</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>4</td><td>1,800</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>5</td><td>3,200</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>6</td><td>5,000</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>7</td><td>7,200</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>8</td><td>9,800</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>9</td><td>12,800</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>10</td><td>16,200</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>11</td><td>20,000</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>12</td><td>24,200</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>13</td><td>28,800</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>14</td><td>33,800</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>15</td><td>39,200</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>16</td><td>45,000</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>17</td><td>51,200</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>18</td><td>57,800</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>19</td><td>64,800</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>20</td><td>72,200</td></tr>\n		</tbody></table>\n		<h3>\n			Girl/Witch Friendship Levels\n		</h3>\n		<table>\n		<tbody><tr><td><b>Level</b></td><td><b>Total Zeny</b></td></tr>\n		<tr><td>1</td><td>0</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>2</td><td>100</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>3</td><td>400</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>4</td><td>900</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>5</td><td>1,600</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>6</td><td>2,500</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>7</td><td>3,600</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>8</td><td>4,900</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>9</td><td>6,400</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>10</td><td>8,100</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>11</td><td>10,000</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>12</td><td>12,100</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>13</td><td>14,400</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>14</td><td>16,900</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>15</td><td>19,600</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>16</td><td>22,500</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>17</td><td>25,600</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>18</td><td>28,900</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>19</td><td>32,400</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>20</td><td>36,100</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>21</td><td>40,000</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>22</td><td>44,100</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>23</td><td>48,400</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>24</td><td>52,900</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>25</td><td>57,600</td></tr>\n		</tbody></table>\n		<p>\n			Friendship levels do continue past 25, with experience following the pattern 100 * PreviousLevel<sup>2</sup>.\n			You get new dialogue up to Level 25, at which you receive Art No. 25 (Girl) or 26 (Witch).\n		</p>\n		<h3>\n			Boy Levels\n		</h3>\n		<table>\n		<tbody><tr><td><b>Level</b></td><td><b>Total EXP</b></td></tr>\n		<tr><td>1</td><td>0</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>2</td><td>50</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>3*</td><td>200</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>4</td><td>450</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>5</td><td>800</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>6</td><td>1,250</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>7*</td><td>1,800</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>8</td><td>2,450</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>9</td><td>3,200</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>10</td><td>4,050</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>11</td><td>5,000</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>12</td><td>6,050</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>13</td><td>7,200</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>14</td><td>8,450</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>15*</td><td>9,800</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>16</td><td>11,250</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>17</td><td>12,800</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>18</td><td>14,450</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>19</td><td>16,200</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>20*</td><td>18,050</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>21</td><td>20,000</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>22</td><td>22,050</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>23</td><td>24,200</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>24</td><td>26,450</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>25*</td><td>28,800</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>26</td><td>31,250</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>27</td><td>33,800</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>28</td><td>36,450</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>29</td><td>39,200</td></tr>\n		<tr><td>30*</td><td>42,050</td></tr>\n		</tbody></table>\n		<p>\n			Boy levels do continue past 30, with experience following the pattern 50 * PreviousLevel<sup>2</sup>.\n			Levels marked with * are those that add an additional point of Pow.\n		</p>\n		<h3>\n			Special Areas\n		</h3>\n		<p>\n			Besides the stationary NPCs you can talk to, there are a few unique things to find around town.\n		</p>\n		<p>\n			District 15 Block 10:\n			tachi (Gives Art No. 22)\n		</p>\n		<p>\n			District 9 Block 6:\n			Spirit Photographer (Buy Art No. 23 and 24)\n		</p>\n		<p>\n			District 11 Block 1:\n			Hello? Hell... o? (Get No. 27 to 33 randomly from curtains)\n		</p>\n		<p>\n			District 6 Block 8:\n			<a id = \"strange_text\"\n				data-comment = \"vgperson put it here and i am just copying it over; and how was anyone supposed to figure out that you could hover over HeadLess to find this text anyway? There was no color indication or similar to highlight it!\"\n				\n				title=\"Hey, thanks for hovering over me. HeadLess is a horror game tachi made about a girl named Erina and a boy named Kenji and some giant HeadLess prisoners. It also features Witch, who is there known as the Red Witch and not hooded - she actually does look pretty young that way. And the highlight of the entire game is a part similar to the \'don\'t hesitate\' part of The Witch\'s House that tries to trick you into thinking the game crashed. But basically, Erina is trying to escape the house where these HeadLess guys are with Kenji, but once she does it turns out she\'s possessed by a Reaper, was in fact the one who decapitated the good-looking guys, and proceeds to decapitate Kenji. Then in a separate scenario, you play as the Red Witch (who was apparently forsaken by everyone she knew and killed them all, making it known as Death Village). She recognizes Erina\'s red \'Reaper eyes\' and wants to help her. She uses her self-immolating powers for some ridiculous hack-and-slashy gameplay and confronts said Reaper, Keros (who is incredibly silly and uses lots of slang), and has a fight with him, and in the good ending everyone lives because of the power of Starlight (AKA deus ex machina), with the heads living simply as heads. No I\'m not translating it.\">\n				HeadLess\n			</a>\n			(Art No. 34 and 35)\n		</p>\n		<p>\n			District 3 Block 8:\n			Girl\'s House (Art No. 36 in storeroom)\n		</p>\n		<p>\n			District 6 Block 2:\n			Bar (Art No. 37 on lower level)\n		</p>\n		<p>\n			District 9 Block 4:\n			Park Bench (Art No. 38)\n		</p>\n		<p>\n			District 11 Block 4:\n			Boy\'s House (Art No. 39 in room)\n		</p>\n		<p>\n			District 8 Block 1:\n			Item Shop (Art No. 40)\n		</p>\n		<p>\n			Lastly, Spirit Queen will give you Art No. 59 if you get 2500 (the original quota and S rank score) on Mission 23.\n			And you get Art No. 60 for clearing Mission 24.\n		</p>\n	</div>\n</div>\";s:6:\"format\";s:9:\"full_html\";s:10:\"substitute\";i:1;}','a:0:{}','a:1:{s:8:\"settings\";N;}','a:0:{}','a:0:{}',0,'a:0:{}','5a62e0ac-036d-4425-92df-fd1c6e4a634c'),(84,24,'bott